    "recap_headline": "The University of Texas at Austin Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AUBURN, Ala. \u2014\nNo. 2 Texas tossed its first-ever shutout in Southeastern Conference play, defeating No. 5 Auburn, 5-0, at Plainsman Park on Sunday afternoon.\nThe Longhorns (20-3, 4-2 SEC) held one of the nation's top teams to just four hits, clinching their first road series win over a top-5 team in five years.\nSophomore left-hander\nDylan Volantis\nset the tone against the Tigers (19-4, 4-2 SEC), pitching four scoreless frames. Volantis totaled four strikeouts, highlighted by an inning-ending punchout that stranded a pair in the second.\nFreshman righty\nSam Cozart\n(4-0) picked up where Volantis left off, twirling 2 2/3 hitless frames of his own. Cozart retired six of the first seven batters he faced, collecting three strikeouts.\nRedshirt junior southpaw\nEthan Walker\n, freshman right-hander\nBrett Crossland\nand senior righty\nMax Grubbs\nteamed up to record the final eight outs to earn the victory.\nTexas' offense backed the staff from the onset, as\nCasey Borba\nblasted a two-run shot over the 37-foot monster in left. The go-ahead jack in the second marked Borba's seventh home run in the last 11 games.\nIn the fourth,\nCarson Tinney\ndoubled the Longhorns' lead with a two-strike, two-out, base hit to right. Tinney's two-RBI single padded the advantage to 4-0.\nTexas pushed\u00a0across its fifth and final tally one inning later, capitalizing on a bases-loaded threat.\nThe Longhorns continue their four-game road swing at Houston on Tuesday. First pitch is scheduled for 6:30 p.m. at Schroeder Park.",
